commit.message:
tidy up the top-level directory

m/ - man pages
p/ - packaging files
s/ - source code
t/ - tests

tests/setup does setopt clobber

it's not clear to me how this worked four years ago when i developed
and used this on my work laptop with archlinux: i definitely had my
usual dotfiles on that one, and my .zshenv has had `setopt noclobber`
in it for over 15 years now...

omit passwords from remote urls

no need for the noise

obscure passwords in remote urls

fixes https://github.com/roman-neuhauser/git-mantle/issues/4

tests/setup: fix sed in headeronly

BSD sed doesn't like "0" as address ("1" is fine
in both BSD and GNU sed).  simplified it a bit
while i was there.

GNUmakefile: do not clobber $PATH

originally introduced to work around idiosyncracies
in my development environment, breaks the process
on *BSD systems.
specfile: Requires += git, BuildRoot gone
README text moved to BLURB, README shadows manpage
manpage: SYNOPSIS mentions -h, --help
add INSTALL file
manpage mentions license
GNUmakefile: sanitize $PATH
GNUmakefile: drop zshisms and obfuscating indirection

PKGBUILD: make gets PREFIX=/usr

the makefile defaults to /usr/local

PKGBUILD: checkdepends += zsh

let's be thorough

git bc: avoid "1 deletion(-)" in summary

git 1.7.1 always used plural here.  i could match these
lines with a regex but that's bad for reading and patching
the tests.

git bc: tests compensate for different --summary

the pipes have more spaces to their right in git-1.7.1.

git bc: git diff-tree s/--find-renames/-M/

the long option --find-renames was apparently added
after 1.7.1 so let's use the less obvious -M.
git bc: `rev-list --count` is a post-1.7.1 feature

git bc: on a branch yet to be born

git-1.7.1 rejects all attempts to change the branch name
in a repository with no commits.

git bc: git config w/o --local

git config --local is a post-1.7.1 addition.

partial fix for RHEL-6.

git-config(1):

> When writing, the new value is written to the repository local
> configuration file by default, and options --system, --global,
> --file <filename> can be used to tell the command to write to
> that location (you can say --local but that is the default).
git bc: git symbolic-ref w/o --short

git bc: avoid git show --no-patch

it was apparently introduced in 1.8.4 and i'd like to support
git versions older than that.

(partial) fix for openSUSE-12.3, SLE-11-SP3 and RHEL-7.

still does not work in RHEL-6: git-1.7.1 craps itself on
branchnames with slashes (not qualified branchnames!).
package builds run the tests

GNUmakefile: 'check' target depends on 'most' *or* 'all'

'most' when $(ALL_INCLUSIVE) is unset, "" or "0", 'all' otherwise.
readability++: literal TAB -> $'\t'

drop outdated, misleading comment

is there any other kind?
drop $cids, $parents is sufficient
GNUmakefile: s/git-mailz/$(name)/ in $(sources)
